import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    zip_count = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='zip_code', data=zip_count)
    chart.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    city_zip_counts = data['city'].value_counts().head(20)
    ax = sns.barplot(x=city_zip_counts.index, y=city_zip_counts.values)
    ax.set(xlabel='City', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    county_state_counts = data.groupby(['state', 'county']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    state_counts = county_state_counts.groupby('state')['county'].count().reset_index(name='num_counties')
    state_counts_sorted = state_counts.sort_values('num_counties', ascending=False)
    
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='num_counties', data=state_counts_sorted, palette='viridis')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of counties across different states?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame, state: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    filtered_data = data[data['state'] == state]
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=filtered_data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude for a specific state?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

state = 'CA'  # Replace with the desired state
chart = plot(data, state)
chart.show()
